org.spongepowered.api.world.gen.populator

Interface Dungeon

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Populator

    public interface Dungeon
extends Populator
    Represents a Populator which places 'Dungeon's randomly underground. Each dungeon has some associated MobSpawnerData, and data regarding the contents of any chests generated within the dungeon.

      A builder for constructing Dungeon populators.

      • getChoices

        Optional<WeightedTable<EntityArchetype>> getChoices()

        Gets a weighted collection of possible EntityArchetypes that could be spawned. One type is chosen when creating the dungeon, for more complex spawners see getMobSpawnerData().

        Note: Only one of choices or mob spawner data will be present.

        Returns:
        Weighted table of possible types, if present

      • setChoices

        void setChoices(WeightedTable<EntityArchetype> choices)

        Sets the possible EntityArchetypes that could be spawned. One type is chosen when creating the dungeon, for more complex spawners see setMobSpawnerData(MobSpawnerData)

        Note: Only one of choices or mob spawner data will be present.

        Parameters:
        choices - Weighted table of possible types

      • getPossibleContents

        LootTable<ItemStackSnapshot> getPossibleContents()
        Gets a mutable weighted collection of possible contents of the chests. Items will be randomly selected from this list based on weight in order to calculate the contents of chests placed within the dungeon.
        Returns:
        The contents list
